<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I also haven&apos;t read this book but the synopsis sounds remarkably similar to the 2005 film The Interpreter, which has a female protagonist (Nicole Kidm<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">‚Ä¶more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I also haven't read this book but the synopsis sounds remarkably similar to the 2005 film The Interpreter, which has a female protagonist (Nicole Kidman). The movie has similar plot elements: A protagonist draws on languages learned through a childhood in Central Africa to build a career as a high-powered diplomatic translator and in the course of this work accidentally overhears a nefarious scheme that implicates the highest tiers of political power: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Interpreter">http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Inte...</a><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
