</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1824297-i-wondered-did-anyone-have-a-problem-with">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/962322-dennis"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1430584962i/962322._UX100_CR0,2,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/962322-dennis">Dennis</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">My problem with Salvo is that he was an idiot so it stood to reason that he didn&apos;t know what dirty was, or how pointless his idealism was. In this sen<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">‚Ä¶more</a></span><span class="fullContent">My problem with Salvo is that he was an idiot so it stood to reason that he didn't know what dirty was, or how pointless his idealism was. In this sense, he wasn't a traitor because he felt he was protecting the Congo and the UK and didn't seek to gain anything out of it for himself. Just my opinion...<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
